      "writtenOn": "2020-07-20T17:28:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In theory this is possible but in practice it does not seem to happen today. The typical logic is \"can I do this optimization \u0026\u0026 can a subset of my children do it\". Hypothetically, in a scenario with several chained randomly-selected FPs, you could get these sorts of low-probability outcomes. I added an upper limit of 2000 trials, which prints a SkDebugf warning with the random seed when it triggers.",
